Description: Fragment of oval handle to sharp turn of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay near fine pink-buff; cream slip.
Production date: 124 BC (see N. Badoud, Le temps de Rhodes, 2015, 143.)
Curator's comments: Name Teisamenos. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 184, 9. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0216.35.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1145)
